<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="Publisher" Owner="NLM"><PMID Version="1">41891718</PMID><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>03</Month><Day>27</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">2576-098X</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Mar</Month><Day>27</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Microbiology resource announcements</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Microbiol Resour Announc</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Draft genome sequence of <i>Enterococcus faecalis</i> BFS29 isolated from diseased silver carp (<i>Hypophthalmichthys molitrix</i>) in Bangladesh.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>e0128625</StartPage><MedlinePgn>e0128625</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1128/mra.01286-25</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>We report a draft genome sequence of <i>Enterococcus faecalis</i> BFS29, isolated from a diseased silver carp in Bangladesh. The 2.89 Mb genome assembled into 69 contigs with a GC content of 37.4%, encodes 2,789 predicted coding sequences, and contains virulence, antimicrobial resistance, and bacteriocin-associated genes.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Babu</LastName><ForeName>Md Rony</ForeName><Initials>MR</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Institute of Biotechnology and Genetic Engineering, Gazipur Agricultural University, Gazipur, Bangladesh.</Affiliation><Identifier Source="RINGGOLD">198780</Identifier><Identifier Source="ROR">https://ror.org/04tgrx733</Identifier></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Saha</LastName><ForeName>Promi</ForeName><Initials>P</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Institute of Biotechnology and Genetic Engineering, Gazipur Agricultural University, Gazipur, Bangladesh.</Affiliation><Identifier Source="RINGGOLD">198780</Identifier><Identifier Source="ROR">https://ror.org/04tgrx733</Identifier></AffiliationInfo></Author>